<br>
She's a worshipper of Bertoxxulous, and thus on the Bloodsaber faction.  There's a number of minor quests in the Qeynos area that are done to raise faction with various groups, many of which lower Bloodsaber faction.  I know I did some of them when I was lower level, so my faction was below starting level.  Several enchanters have mentioned that they had to either multi-quest this section with a friendly necro, or kill various NPC's to raise Bloodsaber faction, which trashed the rest of their Qeynos factions.  I decided to try raising it without becoming KOS to the rest of the city.<br>
<br>
I checked out Allakhazam's and found a quest that looked promising.  I went back and forth between North and South Qeynos doing &quot;The Crate&quot; quest(evil version), trying to raise Bloodsaber faction.  Note that this quest has 2 parts, and each side has one negative faction hit that has a positive on the other side.  These hits are NOT equal in size, however, and you will lose faction with the good guards of Qeynos and the Circle of Unseen Hands (Thieves Guild).<br>
<br>
The Bloodsaber faction hit is the last in the list, and thus the smallest change, so I suspect it's really very slow to improve.  Still, it was going up, so I did a brief recon to check it out.<br>
<br>
I zone in to the Qeynos Aqueducts while invisible. I click on a guard and move around the corner, and drop invis. He Cons green and dubious. Ok, not KOS and I can work with that. Let's try illusions. Human and Imp bring me up to Apprehensive, not bad. I try Skeleton, figuring these undead worshippers will love that.<br>
<br>
Back to dubious. Huh? Undead worshippers that that don't like undead?  I try going invis and past the guard, clicking on the skeleton down the hall. Mr. Bones is also dubious, so I switch back to looking human. I'm back to apprehensive. Ok, now we have a skeleton who likes humans more than he likes other skeletons.   Mr. Bones needs some therapy for those self-esteem issues. Cast my faction altering spell on the lowbie guard, and he's amiable. Move in, checking as I go and everyone is amiable, including Mr. Bones. Hail my NPC, get my item and gate out, mission accomplished.<br>
<br>
So, while the faction quest was working, I'm not sure how bad I was with them before. I thought it would be a pain, since I saw a lot of messages from enchanters in various forums stating that they needed to fix faction or multi quest, and I know I did a few quests early on that dropped Bloodsaber faction. Even so, I was able to walk in and out with no trouble.<br>
<br>
As a side note, the faction for the Corrupt Guards is quite good. I started amiable and I'm am now ally with them. I dropped from Ally to Warmly with the good guards, and from Indifferent down to Apprehensive with the Thieves Guild, but I'm planning to hunt a few bandits in the Karanas when I get the chance, so that should be easily fixable. Merchants are up to Ally as well, but they were high Warmly before.<br>
All in all, I'm pretty happy.<br>
<br>
I think we should try to cheer up Mr. Bones though. Maybe send him an X-Ray of Buffy?<br>
<br>
